post_text:
Good Morning Irish Community!
Tomorrow morning, July 25th, we will celebrate our seniors and send them off with good wishes. Join us at 10:00 am for a Class of 2020 parade. The parade will begin at the District Gym parking lot. The seniors in vehicles will travel south on Marshall Street. From Marshall they will travel West on 5th street. They will then head north on Nicholson before they turn back East on 7th street.

We will have three places where you can hear the students be introduced to include: Chapman Middle School, the corner of 5th and
Marshall and Chapman High School.

We hope the community will come to the parade. Bring your signs. Honk your horns. Wave at our seniors. And remain six feet apart!

See you in the morning! We are proud of the Class of 2020. 💚

post_text:
The National FBLA Conference that was originally scheduled to be in Salt Lake City, Utah this summer was converted to a virtual conference from June 29th - July 1st. Emma Frieze, senior, attended from her home and created a video submission of her Electronic Career Portfolio. After breaking into the final round last week, today she was awarded 5th place in the nation. She has qualified and attended National FBLA all four years of her high school career, placing in three different events.

Congratulations, Emma!
📸: Sue Frieze

post_text: Proud of our Salina Tech CNA students for finishing their clinicals this summer. We are thankful for our partnership with Salina Area Technical College and the programs and opportunities they offer our students.
shared_text:
Salina Area Technical College
June 22 at 7:52 PM ·

When Kansas schools shut down in March, Certified Nurse Aide students in area high schools were unable to complete their hands-on clinical training. Now they're coming back to the Salina Tech campus for several intense days of practice ahead of their State Boards testing on July 1.
Wish them luck!

Our final recognition this week is the "Excellence in Education" award. Each year, our National Honor Society members vote on a staff member and recognize them for their work within the field of education. This year, our NHS voted on this award in February before we moved to an online learning environment. As you will see in this video, the staff member they recognized and sentiments shared by our students have proven to be very true in this difficult time.

Congratulations to Jennifer Tiller. Our winner of the "Excellence in Education" award winner for 2020. Presented by Valerie Rodriguez, NHS President.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C-JMq7H47J4

post_text:
It is "Teacher Appreciation Week" and we cannot think of a staff that deserves more appreciation than the staff at CHS. They have been nationally recognized by being one of the best 4A schools in the State of Kansas.

Recognized for our Irish Hub, School Run Businesses, Exceptional Fine Arts Programs, Second to None CTE programs, and Standards Based Grading...Chapman High School teachers are truly innovators in the field of Education. In the face of a global pandemic, they have worked tirelessly to support our students as best they can from home.

As you drive through our community, you will see signs that recognize the teachers of Chapman High School who go above and beyond.

Shout out to the teachers of CHS!

post_text:
Irish Hub is back!

We might not be at CHS but our philosophy remains the same. If you, or your student, is struggling in classwork we want to help. Parents and/or students can sign their student up for online tutoring.

Use the form below for students (and parents) to sign up to receive tutoring by NHS students. Tutoring times are Tuesday and Thursday from 2:00-3:00pm. Tutoring will be conducted using Zoom. Please sign up by 1pm on the day you wish to receive tutoring. Mrs. Cook will send you a zoom invite by email to join the Irish Hub Tutoring Zoom.

http://www.chapmanirish.net/continuouslearning/irishhub/

We will then provide feedback to your teachers after the tutoring has taken place to let them know how it went. A big thanks to Mrs. Cook, the NHS, our para educators, Mr. Mayer and Mr. Bell for helping us maintain this important program!

Tutoring starts tomorrow!

post_text:
Today is the day! Chapman High School is releasing their plan for Continuous Learning. We ask before we release these plans that you watch the following video for a brief overview and message from our CHS Administrators: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iUy9JRYbSGA&t=49s

Chapman High School is releasing their plan for Continuous Learning. We are abiding by a three S idea. The first S is for Schedule. This is a suggested daily/weekly schedule for your student. The second S is for Suggestions. We have put together a list of suggestions that we believe will help students be more successful during this time. The third S is for Stuck? If you are stuck or confused as to what our schedule entails please read the Q&A with the High School Administration.

All of these documents along with tutorials for technology support (including how to reset your chromebook) can be found at our new website: http://www.chapmanirish.net/continuouslearning/

post_text:
We saw many of your questions based on the closure of Chapman High School from March 14th- March 29th. We have tried to answer the questions that we currently have answers to at this time.

Question: Is Chapman High School closed?
Answer: Yes, our buildings are closed to the public, staff and students until March 30th.

Question: Can students travel to Salina Tech?
Answer: No.

Question: Are you still having the prom and SADD after prom?
Answer: Yes, the prom has been tentatively rescheduled for May 2nd.

Question: Are we still having a choir concert?
Answer: At this time it is postponed.

Question: Will graduation take place on May 17th?
Answer: Still to be determined.

Question: Will we have spring sports practices between March 14th and March 29th?
Answer: No.

post_text:
Each year leading up to the Chapman vs. Abilene game we raise money for a community member in need.

This year, all proceeds raised by the two schools will go to Adrian Williams, a 4th grade student at Blue Ridge Elementary School. This summer Adrian was diagnosed with Non-Hodgkins Burkitt Lymphoma. Adrian has two sisters who attend Chapman High School.

Student Council will be placing luminaries on the path into the stadium to honor Cancer Fighters. If community members wish to purchase a luminary please e-mail agruen@usd473.net for further details or stop inside the CHS office.

post_text:
The CHS and CMS Clay Trap Shooting team competed at the State Tournament in Wichita on Saturday, June 15th. Over 1800 students participated out of the 74 schools. Chapman competed in the 1A division and posted some of their best scores of the season individually. Results out of 100 targets:
Langdon Elliott-Varsity 96 (Tied for 9th for Varsity Males)
Cheyanne Ballay-Varsity 95 (2nd among Varsity Female Division)
Cooper Lewis 82 Jr. Varsity
Mason Barnum 81 Jr. Varsity
Hunter Picking 78 Jr. Varsity
Travis Leasure 76 (Tied for 18th place in Novice Males)
Luke Struber 75 Jr. Varsity
Congratulation on a successful 2nd year of the program!

Next school year is rapidly approaching!
We are now accepting Flower of the Month Club memberships! Receive a monthly floral arrangement created by our students. This also helps them learn new techniques and design forms for classroom instruction as well!
Need an ongoing gift for a spouse, family member, or friend? This is a great way to show someone you appreciate them!
We would love to work with local community members to create monthly arrangements. All is takes is one initial payment to help fund projects each month for our students.

For more information check out the flyer or email Mrs. Anderes at janderes@usd473.net

post_text:
Chapman High School Bulletin for Monday, May 6th to Saturday, May 11th

Great Season for the Forensics team who took 3 students to State Champs and 5 students to State Festival. Senior Madeline Elliott has qualified for State Champs all four years. Naliya Contreras came home with two 1st place ratings and Rylee Lott with a Gold Medal.

Monday Sports: NCKL Golf @ Wamego 1pm, Rescheduled Varsity Baseball/Varsity Softball/JV Softball @ Abilene 4:30pm

Tuesday Sports: Varsity Baseball/Varsity Softball/JV Softball at home vs. Wamego 4:30pm - Baseball and Softball Senior Recognition will take place after the first game is finished.

Wednesday: We leave for the High Honor Roll Trip at 7:30am on the Northside of the HS and return for buses at 3:28pm. Food is provided for free at Kansas City Powerplay's buffet. A card will be provided to you with 2 main activities and points for games. You can bring extra money to add on.

Thursday: The 3 Sport Athlete Recognition and food will start at the high school commons at 6:30pm.

Friday Sports: Varsity and JV Track NCKL at Clay Center 3pm

post_text:
Tonight we are hosting our annual FFA BBQ, CHS CTE Showcase and Class Night.

The FFA BBQ will run from 4:30 to 7:30 in front of CHS. Tickets at the door are $10. You receive a 1/2 Chicken, baked beans, chips, pickle, homemade roll, ice cream, and bottled water

CTE Showcase will take place in the shop and commons area of CHS. Mr. Wendel's classes will showcase their projects in the shop. Ms. DeArmond's Irish Ink students will have their portfolios and projects on display. Mr. Weller will be displaying IrishFABrication. Mrs. Anderes will be having plant sales from after school until 7:00pm.

Finally, stay for the Class of 2019 "Lights Camera Class Night." It begins at 8:00 pm in the CHS Auditorium. Tickets are $5 at the door.

We have great things going on at CHS and hope to see the community this evening.

Our Future Business Leaders Association (FBLA) had an awesome showing at State FBLA for the past two days!

Madeline Elliot- 8th Advertising, 3rd E-Business, and 4th in Sales Presentation
Emma Frieze- 1st in Business Communication, and 1st in Job Interview
Paige Howard-3rd in Emerging Business Issues
Braydon Schmidt and Katelyn Reiff- 2nd in Graphic Design

Katie Locke had a great day at the Kansas Student Technology Leaders competition. She placed 1st in Website Design!

Congratulations to all our future business leaders and technology specialists!
